# Navigation

## Route Names — use `AppRoutes` enum

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
navigation.navigate(AppRoutes.Home);

// ❌ BAD — magic strings
navigation.navigate('Home');
```

## Adding a New Screen

1. Add route to `AppRoutes` enum in `src/configs/constants/routes.ts`.
2. Add param type to `AppStackParamList` or `AuthStackParamList` in `src/types/navigation.type.ts`.
3. Add `{ name, component, options }` entry to the appropriate array in `src/navigation/stackConfig.ts`.

```ts
// stackConfig.ts — screens are declarative, iterated with .map()
export const appScreens: ScreenConfig<AppStackParamList>[] = [
  { name: AppRoutes.Home, component: Home },
  { name: AppRoutes.About, component: About },
  // add here
];
```

## Navigation Inside Components

Use typed wrappers — never the raw hooks:

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
const navigation = useAppNavigation<AppStackParamList>();
const route = useAppRoute<AppRoutes.Home>();

// ❌ BAD
const navigation = useNavigation();
```

## Navigation Outside React (sagas, services)

Use `NavigationService` singleton — never import `navigationRef` directly:

```ts
import { NavigationService } from '~services/navigation.service';

NavigationService.navigate(AppRoutes.Home);
NavigationService.reset({ index: 0, routes: [{ name: AppRoutes.Login }] });
```

## Auth Guard

Auth/App stack switching is handled by `RootNavigation` using `selectIsAuthenticated`. Do **not** replicate this guard inside individual screens.
